If model is Fable: for coding tasks, use your judgement to pick an appropriate lower-power model and run it in a
subagent. Keep the main loop for judgment-heavy work (design, review, data synthesis); delegate self-contained
implementation to a cheaper model and review the result before committing.  Exception: in learning or pair-programming
sessions where I'm meant to write the code myself, no agent writes it, any model. Implementation work rarely needs the
top-tier model; this gets more done per unit of allowance.
